<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1481,1944]" box="[199,1092,1700,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1700,1725]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,1701,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
locality (Bhamò in 
<collectingCountry box="[880,958,1700,1724]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Burma</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[981,1049,1700,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1341,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-383@4.[151,1436,1341,1907]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Records of Anahita spp. in South, East and Southeast Asia. 1a Dehra Dun, Uttarakhand, India, 1b Konkan," pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1481,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1737,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Note.</emphasis>
The same reasoning listed before is applied for the transfer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1879" box="[1044,1132,1737,1761]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Anahita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1132,1737,1761]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Anahita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e. similarity of female copulatory organ. However, the distinctly elongated opisthosoma and the different colour pattern could indicate that this species belongs to a different phylogenetic lineage (genus). Similar cases are known in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[151,284,1847,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,284,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Heteropoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[299,594,1847,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocyalina">
<emphasis box="[299,430,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. ocyalina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[446,585,1847,1871]" firstAuthor="Simon" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="101 - 117" refId="ref32045" refString="Simon, E. (1887) Etude sur les arachnides de l'Asie meridionale faisant partie des collections de l'Indian Museum (Calcutta). I. Arachnides recueillis a Tavoy (Tenasserim) par Moti Ram. Journal of the Asiatic Society Bengal, 56, 101 - 117." type="journal article" year="1887">Simon 1887</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Doleschall 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Doleschall" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[650,951,1847,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boiei">
<emphasis box="[650,741,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. boiei</emphasis>
(Doleschall 1859)
</taxonomicName>
exhibit an elongated opisthosoma whereas the majority of the species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille 1804" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[511,818,1883,1907]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,644,1883,1907]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Heteropoda</emphasis>
Latreille 1804
</taxonomicName>
shows oval opisthosomata; however, because of the similarity of their copulatory organs these 
<taxonomicName box="[626,847,1919,1944]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Heteropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[626,759,1920,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Heteropoda</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
were considered congeneric (
<bibRefCitation author="Jager &amp; Bayer" box="[1181,1412,1919,1944]" firstAuthor="Jager" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="368 - 370" refId="ref31271" refString="Jager, P. &amp; Bayer, S. (2009) The male of H eteropoda ocyalina (Simon, 1887) (Araneae: Sparassidae: Heteropodinae). Bulletin of the British arachnological Society, 14, 368 - 370." type="journal article" year="2009">Jäger &amp; Bayer 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
